    "This type of condition is classical to analyze the asymptotics of Bayesian estimators in statistics (Ghosal and Van der Vaart, 2017).",
    "Proof: The proof mimics the strategy of Example 4.7, but in a more general setting.",
    "We define, for any r > 0, ρ r as the restriction of π to {θ ∈ Θ: R(θ) -R(θ *) ≤ r}.",
    "We put r = d π /β.",
    "Note that as β ≥ d π /r 0, r ≤ r 0 and thus"
  ]
